name: Jeremy Harwell
bio: Wedding & Editorial Lensman / Film & Digital / Martha Stewart Weddings and Condé Nast Bride’s Top Wedding photographer.

social_posts.post_text: I’m so honored to be named one of 50 top wedding photographers by @brides Thank you to all my wonderful clients, my wedding planner friends and to all those who have supported me, I could not do this without your trust and generosity! A special thanks to my associate @scottasano who has been a dedicated colleague and friend, this is our shared honor.

It’s been an amazing year of wonderful couples, planners, and weddings! Thank you to all my colleagues, friends, family and most especially, my clients who trusted me with their most sacred day! I’m so enriched by knowing y’all and telling your stories. Thank you @brides for the honor!
I loved photographing this beautiful Williamsburg, Virginia wedding at the bride’s alma mater, William & Mary.
The most beautiful souls married this weekend! Congratulations Taylor & Seth!

This was such an incredible weekend planned flawlessly by @gatheringevents I’m so thankful for my team and the opportunity to work with such an amazing family who are the epitome of Southern grace and charm. Congratulations Carolyn & Chris!
Who else loves variety in bridesmaids dresses?
These two are a match made in heaven! I’m so lucky to document their love!
It was a magical weekend with @browneandtowers Congratulations Alexandra & Bobby, Y’all are wonderful!
My heart was made so happy this weekend from photographing this wonderful, authentic and loving couple! Congratulations Sahana & Jack!
A perfect wedding day in Cashiers, NC. Congratulations Grace & Jack!
It was such a beautiful weekend celebrating Clair & Patrick! Northern Michigan is a magical place and I’m so lucky to document love & weddings!
The most beautiful wedding weekend celebrating Lindsay & Kyle!
Happy Forever, Kenisha & Stephen!
Congratulations Cara & Dave, Your love is inspiring!

This wedding is so special, because this couple and their families are precious. Also special because of the giant storm we all went through together and came out the other side into joy and light. Congratulations Mary & Owen, y’all are loved!
Congratulations to Courtney & Aram who married this week in Highlands, NC.
I loved my time with these two at the Swan House! I’m so excited for their wedding later this year.
Congratulations Kylie & Paul! What a beautiful weekend in Amelia Island!
Congratulations Micah & David! It was such an honor to be your wedding photographer!
An amazing wedding day with @browneandtowers Congratulations Haley & Michael!
Congratulations Sae & Marco!
Love these two so much! Congratulations Hannah & Jeremy!
A timeless and perfect weekend for these two amazing humans! Congratulations Brinkley and Anderson!
Holga Party Pics #holga
The most beautiful autumnal wedding with @toast_maren Congratulations Jenn & Nick!
The sunniest wedding in spite of the weather! All because of these two and their joyous families and friends! Congratulations Mary Winston & Kevin!

The sacredness of family. I have known these dear people since before they were married and began their family. Now they are five, everyday choosing love, selflessly, unconditionally. The children grow and thrive and each day the bonds grow stronger. Adversity, merely a means to grow deeper, closer and more resilient. Being a documentarian is incredibly enriching, however, it requires patience and a willingness to observe, watch and join the energy. Being present in the moment. Children’s energy is very simple, pick up a stick, put pebbles in a fountain, and walk by the water. In their enjoyment of simplicity, comes the lesson. Slow down, go outside, take a walk and help your little brother up the hill. Happy Holidays!
Wedding & Editorial Lensman / Film & Digital / Martha Stewart Weddings and Condé Nast Bride’s Top Wedding photographer.
